---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="The Proposed 28th Amendment - USCitizenship2032" description="Full text of the proposed constitutional amendment to modernize U.S. birthright citizenship, with plain-English explanations.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container text-center max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-gold-500 font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-4">Proposed 28th Amendment</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-warm-white mb-6">The Full Proposal</h1>
      <p class="text-warm-white/80 text-lg">
        Four sections. Clear rules. It protects sovereignty, protects children, and protects everyone born before 2032.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Amendment Text -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">

      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">1</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">Qualified Citizenship at Birth</h2>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gold-500 bg-charcoal text-warm-white pl-6 pr-6 py-5 rounded-r-lg mb-6 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed italic">
          "Citizenship at birth is conferred only to persons born within the United States who have at least one parent who is a United States Citizen or a Lawful Permanent Resident at the time of birth."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">What this means:</p>
          <p class="text-near-black leading-relaxed">
            If you are born in the U.S. and at least one of your parents is a citizen or green card holder, you are a citizen at birth. This is how it already works in the UK, Australia, New Zealand, and most of Europe.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">2</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">The 10-Year Path to Citizenship</h2>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gold-500 bg-charcoal text-warm-white pl-6 pr-6 py-5 rounded-r-lg mb-6 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed italic">
          "Children born in the United States to non-qualifying parents shall be granted protected Registered Resident status. This status shall automatically convert to full United States Citizenship upon:
          <br><br>
          (a) Completion of ten years of continuous residency within the United States, verified through school enrollment, tax, or other public records; or
          <br><br>
          (b) A parent obtaining United States Citizenship while the child is under the age of eighteen."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">What this means:</p>
          <p class="text-near-black leading-relaxed">
            If neither parent qualifies, the child is not left in limbo. They get protected status from day one. After growing up in America for 10 years, going to American schools and living in American communities, they become a full citizen automatically. No application. No fee. No waiting in line. Australia already does almost exactly this.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gold-50 border border-gold-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-gold-700 mb-2">Why this matters:</p>
          <p class="text-near-black leading-relaxed">
            This puts the Dream Act into the Constitution. No child who grows up in American schools will ever be deported. That protection would be written into the highest law of the land. No president can undo it with an executive order.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">3</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">No Child Left Without a Country</h2>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gold-500 bg-charcoal text-warm-white pl-6 pr-6 py-5 rounded-r-lg mb-6 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed italic">
          "The United States shall grant citizenship at birth to any person born within its territory who would otherwise be rendered stateless."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">What this means:</p>
          <p class="text-near-black leading-relaxed">
            If a child is born on U.S. soil and would have no citizenship anywhere in the world, the U.S. steps in. No child born here will ever be a person without a country. Most developed nations already have this same rule.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-white font-bold text-sm shrink-0">4</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold">The Legacy Shield</h2>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-gold-500 bg-charcoal text-warm-white pl-6 pr-6 py-5 rounded-r-lg mb-6 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed italic">
          "This amendment shall take effect on January 1, 2032. All persons born within the United States prior to this date shall retain their citizenship in full. Their status is permanent, irrevocable, and unaffected by this amendment."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-2">What this means:</p>
          <p class="text-near-black leading-relaxed">
            If you were born before January 1, 2032, nothing changes for you. Period. Your citizenship is locked in forever. This only applies to births on or after that date. No surprise changes. No looking backward.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Open Source CTA -->
      <div class="border-2 border-teal-600 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">This text is a draft. Help us make it better.</h3>
        <p class="text-warm-gray mb-6 max-w-lg mx-auto">
          The wording needs to be exact. The full text is on GitHub where lawyers, experts, and regular citizens can review every word and suggest changes.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center">
          <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032/issues/new?template=amendment-feedback.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary">Suggest a Change</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/jtwebman/uscitizenship2032/issues/new?template=legal-analysis.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-secondary">Raise a Legal Concern</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-dark py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="container text-center max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-warm-white mb-4">See How This Compares</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-white/70 text-lg mb-8">
        This is not radical. It is how most of the developed world already works.
      </p>
      <a href="/comparison" class="btn-primary">View 30-Country Comparison</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
